snippet.textDisplay:
"God is our refuge and strength, a very present help in trouble" (Psalm 46:1).
"And we know that all things work together for good to those who love God, to those who are the called according to His purpose" (Romans 8:28). "Behold, I am the LORD, the God of all flesh. Is there anything too hard for Me?" (Jeremiah 32:27).

It's very important to stand strong and not to give in to imagined fear since it can actually weaken our immunity - there is a subtle but intimate connection between the mind and the immune system. It has been reported that our cooperation as a nation (at the levels of communities and sub-communities) can make a significant impact on how well the crisis may be overcome.

We must plead to the Lord for divine intervention since He cares about us. In Him, what seems to be impossible for us can become possible. The discovery of the spike protein is nothing short of grace from the Lord.

In God we trust. May the Lord be exalted.
